MENINGITIS, MENINGOCOCCAL - ITALY (10): FATAL
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Wed 28 Dec 2016
Source: ANSA [edited]
http://www.ansa.it/english/news/general_news/2016/12/28/28-tuscany-meningitis-cases-in-2016_97b796bb-0870-4b02-9884-555f563376df.html


As many as 59 cases of meningitis C have been registered in Tuscany from 2015 to today, authorities said Wednesday [28 Dec 2016] after a Rome elementary-school teacher became the latest victim of the virus [_Neisseria meningitidis_, the cause of meningococcal meningitis is a bacterium, not a virus]: 31 last year [2015] and 28 this year [2016].

12 people have died of meningitis, 6 this year and 6 last, they said. To these must be added a death from meningitis B and the death of a patient affected by another strain, pneumococcal meningitis. The greatest incidence of the virus [sic] was in the 20-29-year-old age bracket, followed by the 0-19-year-old [age] bracket. Only in 19 cases the persons affected were more than 40 years of age. But the average age of those who died was 52 [years].

Tuscany has seen more meningitis deaths than any other Italian region.

